sub_title: Leading United Nations Registered Partnerships for SDGs | Award-winning Entrepreneur | Co-founder of Think Tank AlterContacts | Writer| TED Speaker
summary:
Award-Winning Entrepreneur and Sustainability Leader with 12 years of experience in the field. Co-founder of the Think Tank AlterContacts, leading SDG Acceleration Actions recognized by the United Nations and awarded by the European Parliament. Author of 50+ articles on sustainable entrepreneurship and social innovation, incl. for Barents Encyclopedia and Entrepreneur magazine. Facilitator and guest speaker at 100+ conferences, including the UN MSMEs Day 2021 and UN High-Level Political Forum 2023. Was awarded Gold as Hero of the Year 2020 and 2022 and Woman of the Year in 2021.

profile_positions.description:
AlterContacts acts as a laboratory of impact ideas. Our key services are the facilitation of strategic dialogue and the design of high-impact social initiatives.

Our work is fueled by a network of conscious people in 40+ countries: inventors, scientists, entrepreneurs, TED speakers, independent professionals, world-award winners, PhDs, scientists, and researchers who graduated from distinguished universities, forward-thinking institutions such as the Singularity University and the Institute for the Future.

That allows our partners to leverage knowledge and experience on sustainable solutions for energy, agriculture, infrastructure, economic models, human evolution, nutrition and health, among others.

Our methods to achieve maximum impact using minimum resources are recommended by the United Nations SDG Good Practices Network as "an example to follow and replicate across the globe".

volunteer_experiences.description:
Erasmus for Young Entrepreneurs is a cross-border exchange programme which gives new or aspiring entrepreneurs the chance to learn from experienced entrepreneurs running small businesses in other Participating Countries.

The exchange of experience takes place during a stay with the experienced entrepreneur, which helps the new entrepreneur acquire the skills needed to run a small firm. The host benefits from fresh perspectives on his/her business and gets the opportunities to cooperate with foreign partners or learn about new markets.

ACCELERATING AI STARTUPS AND PREPARING THEM FOR GLOBAL SCALING
AI Program enables tech startups to grow and get ready for global scaling. Rockstart supports entrepreneurs with a strong purpose by connecting them with the brightest minds in the industry. The Rockstart AI Program provides access to the European AI ecosystem, industry/corporate partners, talent, capital, and coaching.
